{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require non-resident parents to be informed of issues relating to their children",
        "additional_details": "At present it is possible for one parent to become involved with a new partner with a history of domestic violence and abuse, and a non-resident parent may not find out or be told even if concerns are raised with the police, social care and school.\r\n \r\nCreating new requirements for non-resident parents to be informed of issues relating to their children could help keep children safe.",
        "background": "The Government should require non-resident parents be told if the resident parent gets a new partner with a record of domestic violence or abuse. Social care and schools should also be required to contact non-resident parents about any concerns regarding their children.",
